But it went public at $32 billion, so in the most important sense =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0for a venture capitalist =E2=80=94=C2=A0you were wrong.
The anti-portfolio page emphasizes the idea=C2=A0that it is embarrassing to=
 turn down an investment that turns out to be good, but it also suggests th=
at there is=C2=A0no=C2=A0need to be embarrassed about the deals you did tha=
t turn out to be bad. The only sins are ones of omission; the lessons learn=
