<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are some public companies where the chie=
f executive officer (and, usually, founder) is also the controlling shareho=
lder. This creates a weird dynamic for those companies=E2=80=99 boards. Wha=
t if the CEO does something bad, and the board concludes that he should no =
longer run the company? Ordinarily, in that scenario, the board would fire =
the CEO. But here the CEO is the controlling shareholder, and he can fire t=
he board.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a correct answer here, which is that,=
 if the board concludes that it is no longer in the best interests of the c=
ompany and its shareholders for the CEO to be in charge, they should fire h=
im. They have a fiduciary duty to run the company with loyalty and care; th=
ey can=E2=80=99t make a decision that they think is wrong just because they=
=E2=80=99re afraid of losing their board seats. Then of course the CEO =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0er, ex-CEO =E2=80=94=C2=A0can fire them, and re-hire himself, <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30210082.274519/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy92aW5jZS1tY21haG9uLXBsb3RzLXJldHVybi10by=
13d2UtMTE2NzI5NTI3MDk_cGFnZT0x/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4d594a92" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 but that=E2=80=99s life</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Vince McMahon, the majority owner and former c=
hief executive of World Wrestling Entertainment Inc., who retired last year=
 amid a misconduct probe, has returned to the company and is pursuing a pos=
sible sale of the business.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. McMahon, who has majority voting power thr=
ough his ownership of WWE=E2=80=99s Class-B stock, said Thursday he had tol=
d the company that he is electing himself and two former co-presidents and =
directors, Michelle Wilson and George Barrios, to the board, confirming an =
earlier Wall Street Journal report. The board had previously rebuffed a mov=
e to reinstate Mr. McMahon.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">WWE said in a news release Friday that Mr. McM=
ahon had removed JoEllen Lyons Dillon, Jeffrey R. Speed and Alan M. Wexler =
from the board. In addition, Ignace Lahoud and Man Jit Singh had resigned a=
s board members, effective Friday, the company said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. McMahon, whose abrupt departure in July 20=
22 followed disclosures by the Journal of multiple payouts to women who had=
 alleged sexual misconduct and infidelity, expects he will be able to assum=
e the role of executive chairman, though he would need board approval for t=
hat, the people said.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">McMahon =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/30210082.274519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmN=
