 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">Wall Street Journal story</a> about venture capital incentive=
s:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Unable to forget their biggest mistakes, some =
venture investors=E2=80=94who by definition are mostly investing in compani=
es before they become successful=E2=80=94are embracing them, talking about =
them, even writing them down. Bessemer Venture Partners, a large San Franci=
sco-based investment firm, popularized the trend with a page on its website=
 dedicated to the =E2=80=9Canti-portfolio.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Clong and storie=
d history has afforded our firm an unparalleled number of opportunities to =
completely screw up,=E2=80=9D declares the Bessemer page.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Naively you might imagine that a VC firm=E2=80=
=99s =E2=80=9Cfailure resume=E2=80=9D would be a list of its worst investme=
nts, but in fact it is a list of the <em>best </em>investments that it was =
offered but did not do. This is, of course, entirely rational.=C2=A0If you =
are a VC, your worst investing decisions will uniformly be the investments =
you did not make; Bessemer=E2=80=99s include=C2=A0passing on early opportun=
ities in Google, Tesla, Apple, Airbnb and Facebook. Investing in some of th=
ose might have brought a 100,000% return. Meanwhile any dumb investment tha=
t you=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>make could have returned, at worst, negative 1=
00%.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: t=
ransparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> If you have a portfolio of 50 investments and 49 of them return negati=
ve 100%, your worst investment decisions were=C2=A0<em>still=C2=A0</em>not =
investing in Google, Tesla, Apple, Airbnb, Facebook, etc. If you=E2=80=99d =
done Facebook, it would have paid for all the mistakes and then some!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But you can sort of see how this mind-set woul=
d have its downsides?=C2=A0</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">John Frankel, a partner at New York-based FF V=
enture Capital, declined a chance to invest in Robinhood at a $10 million v=
aluation. The online brokerage was worth $32 billion when it started tradin=
g on Nasdaq a few years later in 2021.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThese guys were technically incredibl=
y strong, but they knew nothing about marketing and their financial model w=
as ridiculous,=E2=80=9D said Mr. Frankel, who previously held a dozen posit=
ions during a 21-year career at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. =E2=80=9CBut they =
made it. We were wrong. What can I tell you?=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Robinhood Markets Inc. has <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30210082.274519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjL=
mdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTc4Mzg3OS8wMDAxNzgzODc5MjIwMDAw=
NDQvaG9vZC0yMDIxMTIzMS5odG0jaWVlYTEzZGUzMTgzNDQyYmY5ODExZTY1NTE3NTI2MTdmXzE=
5/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6b9774b9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">lost money</a> almost every ye=
ar (it made $7.7 million in 2020); also, for a while it lied to customers a=
bout how it made money using payment for order flow, and eventually <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30210082.274519/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMDcvdGhlLWlwby1t=
YXJrZXQtd2FzLXRvby1nb29kP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTAyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW0=
9ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDExMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ2=
49bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc6321426" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> had to pay a f=
ine</a> to the Securities and Exchange Commission to settle fraud charges. =
If you looked at Robinhood and said =E2=80=9Ctheir marketing is terrible an=
d their financial model is ridiculous,=E2=80=9D in some important senses yo=
u were not wrong. But it went public at $32 billion, so in the <em>most </e=
m>important sense =E2=80=94=C2=A0for a venture capitalist =E2=80=94=C2=A0yo=
u <em>were </em>wrong.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The anti-portfolio page emphasizes the idea=C2=
=A0that it is embarrassing to turn down an investment that turns out to be =
good, but it also suggests that there is=C2=A0<em>no=C2=A0</em>need to be e=
mbarrassed about the deals you did that turn out to be bad. The only sins a=
re ones of omission; the lessons learned are always =E2=80=9Cbe more aggres=
sive.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/30210082.274519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vdGVjaG5vbG9neS91=
